    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="484"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d484">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_JCS1">J.C.S.</gloss> Files: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Combined Chiefs of Staff</gloss> to the
                        Commander in Chief, Allied Force Headquarters</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eisenhower</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quebec</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-20">20 August
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The promising situation existing throughout the Italian area would appear to
                    offer an excellent opportunity by means of 5th Column activities to establish
                    conditions in Sardinia for an unopposed occupation of that island or an
                    unopposed landing on it with Italian help. For Eisenhower <gloss
                        target="#t_Freedom1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Freedom</hi>
                    </gloss> Algiers, <gloss target="#t_Fan1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fan</hi>
                    </gloss> 198, from the Combined Chiefs of Staff. The <gloss target="#t_OSS1"
                        >OSS</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_SOE1">SOE</gloss> organizations might
                    collaborate in accomplishing this. Furthermore this presents an excellent
                    opportunity to test the effectiveness of these organizations and to provide them
                    with experience and training for future operations of a similar character.
                    Corsica also may be worth your attention. Your comments requested and
                    recommendations.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
